76561198062724902,Recommended,270880,29173826,Posted: 10 January,all,LeftClickMadness,"First things first, I personally enjoy this game and will continue to enjoy this game. Something about being alone with the open road, taking jobs across long distances and sightseeing really relaxes me.So let's get into the game!Profile Creation:It's simple, it's quick, there's not a lot of messing around with it. Give you driver a name, choose a picture from hundres both male & female, Pick a logo and name your company and that's pretty much it.Playing the game:So you've made your profile and are ready to get going. You're going to have to take jobs from the job list as you don't have your own truck yet, meaning you're driving somebody else's truck and taking cargo from point A to point B. Once you get your own truck, you'll be taking jobs from the freight market and picking them up yourself and you will earn a bit more for it. There's a bit of a grind and messing with skills but you'll get there eventually.Vehicles:At the time of this review, there are only 4 different types of trucks to purchase: TheKenworth T680,Kenworth W900,Peterbilt 579and thePeterbilt 389. Though there are only 4 trucks, the customization on them is fairly good, but parts are locked and you have to unlock them with ranking up.Skills & Ranking:Every job you complete, you gain experience and money. The experience goes towards a level progress bar and new parts and paints will unlock as you level higher into the game. Every level you progress through will give you a point to use in skills, which can be used forLong Distance Cargo,Fragile Cargo,On Time Delivery,High Value Cargo,Dangerous Cargo(ie: flammable, corrosive or explosive) andFuel Economy.Driving & Parking:Driving with a trailer can be difficult, parking one can be even harder. That's why SCS put in an option to choose between skilled and simple, or if you're truly lazy, skip it entirely(You will lose the added bonus for parking the trailer yourself though)! During your drives, you'll probably find yourself breaking a few laws likeSpeed Offenses,Traffic Light Offenses,Collision Offenses,Wrong Way Offensesand a few others.Overall Pros and ConsPros-Accurate vehicle recreation-Accurate Simulation-Good amount of customization-Lots of roads to travel and places to goCons-AI Traffic can bug out and create traffic jams(that's really all I can think of)First in depth review I've done of a game so hopefully it wasn't too bad. I hope it helped!"
