,Recommended,270880,21595365,"Posted: 2 March, 2016",all,Citybuild122,"So, as a follower of pretty much all of SCS' games, I've pretty much owned all of their games. And I have to say, this game is awesome! So let's go over somethings. First, if you don't like Euro Truck Simulator 2, don't buy this. The GUI's are the exact same and ther only real difference is that this is American. Another thing, if you are impatient and cant do nothing for ten minutes while moving cargo, don't buy this. So, let's get into performance. I own top of the line gaming computers and they have no trouble playing this with every graphics option on high. I own multiple AMD AND NVIDIA gaming computers and they both work perfectly. So AMD Users, don't be afraid. If you have a computer that might not be a gaming computer, I personally don't think I would take the risk. However, you can always get a refund. The graphics (If turned up) are really amazing. And one thing that will make you really impressed is the hills. If you have a solid FPS and I do, going over hills at the same time while turning looks truly amazing. It demonstrates the physics of the game and how much their games have improved.-Pros--Great graphics--Great physics--Realistic--Does not get boring for me--Trucks are awesome--The ability to use pedals,steering wheel, clutch, etc.-Cons--I think that the whole ""Damage"" thing could be better. For example, I think that car accidents could be taken to another level. If a car pulls out in front of me and I hit it and it ruins my load and I don't get paid and then have to pay for my truck, I don't believe that is fair.--Speed limits should be a little less strictHOWEVER, this is beta and for what they have right now, the game is amazing and I definitely would recommend this."
