76561198034025059,Recommended,270880,25064428,"Posted: 21 August, 2016",all,abenson229,"Probably the best thing I can say about ATS is it's one of the most relaxing games I've played in a long time.  You can just work as a driver for hire, with no worries at all other than arriving on time (which isn't difficult) but even if you start your own company, the economy is such that you won't run into too many problems keeping it going.  Or you can just buy a truck for yourself, not hire anyone and cruise the USA (well...CA, NV and AZ) as an independent owner-operator.  Works best with a wheel of course, but perfectly manageable with a gamepad.  There's a ton of options to set so you can make the game as realistic as you wish.  Can't manage or don't want bothered backing a 53' trailer into a tight spot?  Turn it off.  Realistic air brakes to real?  Turn it off, you get the idea.If you enjoy driving games this is worth the $20 easily.  If you don't enjoy driving games this still might be worth the $20, could get you hooked."
