,Recommended,270880,20925139,"Posted: 2 February, 2016",all,DerTebbers,"When viewed as a stand alone game the US$19.99 for a game containing two US states (California and Nevada) and two trucks might seem steep, but there are a few factors to consider. First, SCS has already committed to Arizona and future trucks as free DLC, which is a great long term value. Second, when viewed as a function of the land area open to explore, CA and NV have about 273,000 sq mi of land area, which is about the same as Germany, Austria, Czech Republic, Switzerland, and the UK (and we didn't get all of the UK in ETS2). So while 2 states sounds small, it isn't nearly as small as is seems. Finally, because American Truck Simulator uses the same engine as ETS2 we are getting a game that has many of the bugs already ironed out.Overall, ATS is a great value. Especially when viewed as an expansion of the ETS2 world."
