76561198011358683,Recommended,270880,21015871,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Richards.D,"I have over 100 hrs on ETS2, so I thought I'd write about my experiences with ATS.I live in Canada, so playing ETS2 was fun, but I had no clue whether or not what I was seeing was realistic or authentic. Now, since Canada and the US have very similar city layouts and stores, I was able to judge more ffectively whether or not what I was seeing was convincing. I was delivering a load and saw I was taking it to a grocery store. A big name grocery store, exactly like the ones I've seen accross the US and Canada. Something about this rather mundane experience seemed so immersive and realistic.The building of the store, the parking lot out front, and the loading dock in the back.Now to address the criticism of the lack of content. I do not fault them one bit. I don't want to steal the words of Daniel Hardcastle (Nerd3) so I'll summarize his explanation in this review, as he framed it in the most convincing manner I have heard yet. ETS2 has 2 previous games worth of content behind it, ETS and German Truck Simulator. This is a completely new venture, and the cities are much more fleshed out than in ETS2. So whereas only a few cities actually had many roads, now even smaller cities have a ton of roads and actual area you can drive around in, as opposed to seeing the rest in the distance.At the end of the day, it is NOT a revolutionary change from ETS2. But to anyone who complains of that, I have no idea what you were expecting.Overall, it's a good looking, reasonably priced and actively developing game and I can't be more excited for the future!"
76561198075523846,Recommended,270880,21058671,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,SGT. Renegades,"American Truck Simulator is similar to Euro Truck Simulator 2, but better, Why? ATS acts the same as ETS2, but set in America, driving full on American Trucks!Gameplay (Pros)Now, before the hate comments come in about ATS being the same as ETS2, but set in America. I do agree but alot more, relaxing and more interesting. Now, ATS has 2 states; California and Nevada, Not alot but there is so much to explore and MUCH more detail than pervious SCS games. The cities are more bigger and detailed than ETS2, the environment is stunning and more alive. Like I remember, doing a quick job in Las Vegas I looked over to my right and, there were kids playing at skate park!Environment (Pros)Okay, the scenary is beautiful! Driving through the Nevada desert in my owned Peterbilt, going around Cali is stunning. The amount of detail on this game is amazing. The roads look more rotten and dusty, seeing tumbleweed crossing the roads, birds or whatever they're roaming the skies. Okay, now the cities, what can I say about them? Let me say something; the cities are alot more detailed than ETS2. Like, seriously, then building look more rotten and dirty, there are alot more freedom in them. And more challenging parking areas to manouver your trailer, and with the nose at the front, you're going to hit alot of walls if you don't be careful enough!Eddy's is by far the hardest place to park! Like, Seriously, try and park that trailer behind that wall without hitting anything!Trucks (Pros)Okay, there are only 2 trucks in the game, in whiched they're fully licensed trucks.There are; Peterbilt and Kenworth. Both are good looking trucks and are good starting trucks. I can't tell you much about them, but they're ""Worth"" a try. ;)Okay, now on to Cons.Gameplay(Con)The gameplay acts the same way as ETS2. Get a load, drive it to your destination, unload, BAM DONE! Not only that but, the map isn't that big at all. There are only 2 states in the game; California and Nevada, which isn't impressive, at all. The roads and scenary are a straight copy and paste of the Scandinavia DLC from ETS2. The cities are the same but, bigger and detailed, in fact, there are cities that only have ONE company in it! ONE!Environment (Con)As I said, the environment is a straight COPY AND PASTE of the Scandinavia DLC! Like, seriously, they never put any effort into a new game! Speaking of new game, this should of being a DLC for ETS2. The same game, but with a improved game engine, which is only polished and the same.Trucks (Con)On launch, I was hoping for more than 4 trucks but, there are only 2! Yea, you heard me, 2 trucks! The brands are; Peterbilt and Kenworth and they're boring, to keep on driving over, over and over again!Anyway, that is my review on ATS or American Truck Simulator.This is my honest review on what I think ATS is! But any how, keep on trucking! ;)"
