,Recommended,270880,21176500,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,aramina,"So, things that are unrealistic in this hyper-realistic truck-driving simulator:*The traffic in LA, and Las Vegas is not anywhere near as bad as it is in real life. (This is a good thing)*The intersections of freeways/highways are logical and identical and sane, and not anything like reality. (Also a good thing)*The AI car drivers use their turn signals approx. 10x more often than actual CA drivers. (Thank you lord)*The roads are reasonable in the towns and not anywhere near as maze like as reality. (I've been in a lot of industrial parks in California, the one's in the game are so much saner)*Every single traffic light has a camera to catch you when you ""accidentally"" run a red light. (Annoying, but okay, I guess)*A lot of the major cities are far less impressive and picturesque because of the downscaling. Admittedly, there is stuff in the distance in towns to add depth, but you can't drive there, and I'm usually so busy paying attention to the speed limit I don't notice. (LA didn't bother me much, but Las Vegas was super disappointing compared to the real thing.)Things that are super realistic and awesome:*That moment, where it's 3am and you're driving around Las Vegas looking for a place to sleep and you're staring at your GPS and next thing you know you've plowed straight into the back of a car while going 50mph? Yeah, that was me.*The first time I drove into Primm in game, I was so amazed at how much it was exactly like the real thing that I missed my turn, over-compensated, drove straight into a wall, and caused about 5 car accidents. Seriously, the Primm in-game is identical to the real thing, it's a little creepy.In short, you'll either love this game, or hate it. I find that it's great to play when I've had a long day, I can just turn on some dance music and zone out and drive. That being said, if you don't enjoy the thought of having to follow the speed limit, and follow the basic laws of the road, this probably isn't for you. I'm really hoping and looking forward to future DLC that adds more states, because while I enjoy the fact that I know all these towns, it's a little uncanny."
