,Recommended,270880,21097098,"Posted: 10 February, 2016",all,Disc Milk,"This game, while extremely similar to Euro Truck Simulator 2, fits even better into the mold of traditional American trucking. The actual truck designs are beautiful, and have incredible attention to detail. That being the case, they only have two truck models on offer right now, with a third one coming soon. Although this is due to licensing issues with truck manufacturers, it can be disheartening to players that aren't following the development process so closely.The locations are a similar case to the trucks. There are only two available at the time of this review, including California and Nevada. This is going to be expanded in the future, through DLC (The first state to be added in the future will be Arizona, free of charge). Same as the trucks, while there is a huge increase in polish since ETS2, with tons of detail in the town buildings and structures, having only two states, both being sunny and hot, can really leave a lot to be desired in the way of actual content. You will get lost in the Nevada desert (Not literally lol), you will want to drive around Las Vegas and the beaches of California, but that awe factor runs out after a couple of trips to these few locations, making me want more states to play with.As for right now, the game is pretty much ETS2 with a new, more suitable skin. Whether or not you should buy this over ETS2, or just stick with ETS2 if you've been playing that, is up to whether or not you enjoy the actual theme of American trucks and American locales to be trucking through. Keep in mind that you will have to deal with a lack of content in the beginning of this developmental cycle (with the possibilty of having to pay for future states as DLC). I personally think it is worth it, and I will look forward to any future additions to the game.Good job SCS Software."
