76561198012017193,Recommended,270880,21068839,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,Zwajo,"My impressions of American Truck Simulator after about 5 hours in game.Good:Scenery is good compared to alot of sims out there.Sounds let you really feel the power of the truckroad system is good and makes more sense in some cases than the actual roads.Same solid gameplay of ETS2 fame.Neutral:The game itself is for all intent and purpose still Euro truck sim 2, just with american trucks and map.. so if your a fan of ETS2 its good, if not well this title probably wont be your cup of tea either.Only four trucks... but with quite a few chassis/body options: Personally I prefer this to 20 fake trucks.. you may find it limiting so I list it as a nuetral.Controls I don't have a steering wheel so I can only speak to keyboard.. but the truck don't seem to handle aswell as their ETS2 counterparts. Of course that could also just be my opinion so take it with a grain of salt.Environment; this is different from scenery to me because graphically its nice, but seriously there are more vehicle in america than 1950's cruisers, RV's, Semi's, and cops.Fines: Holy crap police presence. There is no escaping the fines in this game.. ETS2 gave you speed traps that once you learned where they were you could slow down for em. Here? every third car is a cop who can and will pull you over for 4mph over the speed limit. Nice because it forces you to treat it more like a sim... but a tad over done IMO.Bad:Smallish map, I get more is coming out.. I really do.. and I wish I didn't have to list this as a bad.. but when you can run any route before you've even maxed your distance stat.. well thats not beuno.AI; its been a plague on this series even in ETS2 and it didn't get any smarter here.. same stupid 4wheelers doing stupid things right into the side of your truck.TL/DRIf you are a diehard fan of truck games buy it, if you like sims buy it. If you want a finished US map with a 48 states and a total overhaul from ETS2.. well maybe wait awhile and catch it on sale after some more content has released."
