,Recommended,270880,24335106,"Posted: 15 July, 2016",all,nels,"I've spent a lot of time with flying and train sims but never tried a truck sim until  this one was recommended to me. After something like 60 trips I'm still enjoying it, and still learning. The look of the world is quite impressive, really nice to see the world close up and in detail which you don't see while flying and also better than the train sims that I have used. Having never driven anything so large in the real world I'm not sure how accurate the truck physics are. The trucks are kind of underpowered, especially on hills, which I would kind of expect. They do seem to stop to quickly and as a result I still have trouble stopping precisely. The steering takes some getting used to as I find it overly sensitive. I've gotten much better but when starting out I often found myself going back and forth trying to stay in a straight line, and it gets much harder the faster you go. It is quite satisfying, though, to see improvement with practice.What I do find lacking is instruction on proper truck use. I still really have no idea how to park correctly. I'd like to do some of those 90 point ""tough"" parking spots but have no idea how to approach it. Backing up a truck is not natural  so I wish there was a training area or some means of learning this.So, overall a very enjoyable sim and one I would recommend."
