76561198203797316,Recommended,270880,23368335,"Posted: 3 June, 2016",all,ZachOnTak,"American Truck Simulator offers a variety of playing ability in the world of owning a Trucking Business.This simulator allows the player to start off their trucking by working for other companies in order to make money. OR. Players can borrow a bank loan, to immediately make money, which simple deductions being made over time. Grow and develop your own company (which you can name, buy trucks for, and buy garages for) to become the ultimate trucking company in the U.S. (California, Nevada, Arizona so far)WHAT I LIKE --The defualt trucks are the ""kings of the road""-Both Steam and exotic mod support-LOTS of customization for the trucks-Default trailers look amazing-Realism includes fines for disobeying the law, speed limits, traffic lights, traffic, other truck traffic, landmarks (e.g. Golden Gate Bridge) (PLUS A LOT MORE)-Free map expansions (Arizona)-Little to no crashes (unless using a corrupt mod)-No ""super-computer"" needed (runs smoothly on mostly anyting)WHAT I DON'T LIKE--Too many police cars around-Very high citation prices (raised if police are involved or around the incident)-Only 3 default truck designs (unless modded)-Speed limits are high on very twisty roads-Some drop off points are annoyingOverall, American Truck Simulator, or ATS for short, is an amazing game by the SCS Software crew, who were also the creators of ETS and ETS2 (Euro Truck Simulator and Euro Truck Simulator 2)"
