,Recommended,270880,23710191,"Posted: 22 June, 2016",all,[GL] hoopsure,"This is probably one of the best games I've played. Let me make the list.Pros:Realism - Like some others have stated you will bring stuff to where it actually goes, like construction equipment will go to construction site, etc.More Realism - Now I know some people say the AI is broken, but when I play it works really well. They slow down and even stop when your merging onto a highway, they will let you take your turn at a stop sign, as long as you use your turn signals then the AI works great, and much more!Even more Realism - Working mirrors (that you can adjust so you can see out of them better), looking out your window, when it rains you can turn on your wipers and if you don't then you can't see as well out your window, while driving you need fuel, you can get tired (I don't know yet on what happens when your tired haven't had a 24 hour drive yet), traffic offenses (they don't go full on all the laws in the us I don't think because then it would be a little to hard to start), when your in the county you can see crop dusters actually dusting their crops, and lots more.Mod Support - When a game adds mod support it allows the community to really get into the game because they can make content for it for other to use and make their experience more enjoyable. Like say you want a feature in the game but isn't in the game yet/won't be in the game, you can use a mod someone made and have that feature. They even help by letting you know when a mod is incompatible so you don't go searching for hours with tons of mods installed for the mod that breaks your game.Trucking - It's as the title and description say, you're a truck driver. (Idk if this is a spoiler but I'll assume it is) You start off with no money but your a driver for hire, earn enough money to buy your own truck and be your own boss. (Or get a bank loan and buy a truck. :P) I got most of the DLC when I bough the game as most of it is free. (Unless somehow Nevada isn't in yet and I have it for some reason. :P) If you think the drive times will be realistic because the game is very realistic then don't worry, they don't want you to spend 20 hours on one delivery. It goes much faster.And Lots Lots More!Cons:The only con for me is turning needs a tiny bit of work, like I'm use to the wheel auto-correcting when I let got of the turning button but I guess it's more realistic that you have to turn the other way to stop turning.My Opinion of the Game:A must buy if you like a nice relaxing game. Just you and the open road. But is still very fun. And I'll let y'all in on a funny place to sit online, if you go to Oxnard, the GPS takes you a route that most people at one point have no idea how to drive on so there is just a 50 truck pile up. And sometimes someone will be going 100 miles an hour and fly off the cliff. Lol. Definitely recommend this game. Fun times."
