,Recommended,270880,21014127,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Djozar,"Bought this on the request of a friend, who assured me it was much more than 2 trucks and 2 states.  He was right!I was like a lot of people giving bad reviews, at first. ""What the...ONLY 2 trucks?""However, I stopped to think about it. How many different types of trucks do I really see out on the road, myself?I start off with a ""Duty-Day Cab"". Fairly basic. Either Kenworth or Peterbilt. I see other options unlocked as I level, such as lights, mirrors, Sleep-Cabs, wheels. Items to make my truck look like any number of trucks I see out on the roads.Only 2 states. 3rd is coming soon for free. Yeah. Not too thrilled about that as it makes it sound like that's the end of free DLC. We'll have to be patient and hope that's not the case.The 2 states, California and Nevada can take more time to get through at first. I don't have a wheel, just an old xbox360 controller that likes to drift to the right a lot, and going the speed limit, a good job can take a good 10-15 minutes to complete.I'm terrible at backing up and parking. However, this is a good thing, as it's a challenge for me to overcome and get bettwr reards from.The streaming of music is great too. Real radio stations with real bands. Jammed to Megadeth and Volbeat down the Fresno Interstate. It was awesome.The game overall is gorgeous. I don't have much time in it, but I want to see what else there is to it as well.If I had listened to the bad reviews, I would never have picked this up. I do enjoy it for what it is. It's not huge, but it satisfies the curiosity of driving a truck over distances and seeing some cool sights along the way.Maybe not for everyone, but I don't regret it at all.8.5/10"
