,Recommended,270880,20946891,"Posted: 4 February, 2016",all,Hallowenman,"American Truck Simulator is more than just a improved version of Euro Truck Simulator 2. They have added new features like police cars which act as moving speed cameras, different difficulty options in parking so you can choose if you just want easy and simple parking, or try some more difficult parking.Map quality has also been improved a lot from the base ETS2 content. Everything is a lot more detailed, so its no longer just the feeling of driving a big heavy truck that makes the game fun, but also the fact that the sorroundings are beautiful and everything feels alive.SCS really cares about this game, and they are not just gonna abandon it to work on other games. Frequent updates and the fact that they listen to the community is fantastic. The police cars did not accept you driving 1 km/h over the limit at release, but that and other things have been adjusted and fixed.The game is fantastic, and the trucks also feels a lot better to drive than in ETS2. I absolutely recommend this game. But remember this before buying the game:American Truck Simulator is more of a long term investment. You buy the game now and get the content that is avaible now. You dont get all the states in the US at the moment, but by supporting SCS they will be able to add all the states to the game over some time. You will probably have to pay for some map DLCs, maybe all, maybe not all, so this is a sort of investment into getting a huge game completed in the future some time. The base game is not that expensive compared to other titles that might cost $50 + a lot of DLCs."
